ll as the regional context of the events. It brings to light many aspects of this key period in Asian history. Unprecedented in the degree of detail assigned to the story of the Chola expeditions, this volume is also unique in that it includes translations of the contemporary Tamil and Sanskrit inscriptions relating to Southeast Asia and of the Song dynasty Chinese texts relating to the Chola Kingdom.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh1 aKesavapany, K., eeditor.1 aKulke, Hermann, eeditor.1 aSakhuja, Vijay, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Publishing ebook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060668308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066300640uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/9789814345323423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814345323.jpg  a978-3-11-060668-3  ISEAS Publishing ebook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-066300-6  ISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG